answers.body_markdown:
you can create an interface with a method

    void onImageChosen(Bitmap bitmap) 
which will send the image to activity where RecyclerView is added.

    listener.onImageChosen(yourBitmap);
**but it would be better to send path of image instead of full Bitmap.**
And I don&#39;t understand the purpose of your Intent.

When you&#39;ve already got the Bitmap from RecyclerView and it&#39;s in your Activity you can pass it.
To send an existing Bitmap from one Activity to another you can:

    Intent intent = new Intent(this, NewActivity.class);
    intent.putExtra(&quot;BitmapImage&quot;, bitmap);

To get:

    Intent intent = getIntent(); 
    Bitmap bitmap = (Bitmap) intent.getParcelableExtra(&quot;BitmapImage&quot;);

