Consider a place setting in a caf&#233;. Every customer is expected to have a coffee cup as part of the setting, even though that coffee cup is empty. The coffee is optional, but the cup is required. When a customer sits down at that setting, there is a big difference between an empty coffee cup and no cup at all.

So the cup is required to be non-null. But the contents of the cup, the coffee, is optional and is allowed to be null.

    class PlaceSetting {
